opencv
------------------------------------------
OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision) is a library of programming 
functions for real time computer vision. Example applications of the 
OpenCV library are Human-Computer Interaction (HCI); Object 
Identification, Segmentation and Recognition; Face Recognition; Gesture 
Recognition; Camera and Motion Tracking, Ego Motion, Motion 
Understanding; Structure From Motion (SFM); Stereo and Multi-Camera 
Calibration and Depth Computation; Mobile Robotics.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.1-1
  libavcodec52-0.5-1
  libavformat52-0.5-1
  libavutil49-0.5-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libglib2.0_0-2.22.2-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.18.3-1
  libjasper1-1.900.1-1
  libjpeg7-7-10
  liblapack0-3.2.1-1
  libpng12-1.2.35-10
  libstdc++6-4.3.4-3
  libswscale0-0.5-1
  libtiff5-3.9.2-1
  python-2.5.4-10
  zlib0-1.2.3-10

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cmake-2.8.0-11
  cygport-0.9.80-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gcc4-g++-4.3.4-3
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10

Canonical website:
  http://opencv.willowgarage.com/

Canonical download:
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/opencvlibrary/files/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack opencv-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./opencv-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcv-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcv2.0-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/opencv-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

